@page about About

The term `Scan-N-Plan` generally describes a perception-driven approach for performing surface processing manufacturing tasks (e.g., painting, sanding, grinding) in a dynamic, unstructured environment using a robot.

@section supporting_projects Supporting Projects

This repository builds on capabilities from the following supporting projects:

- Sensor Calibration
  - <a href="https://github.com/ros-industrial/industrial_calibration">Industrial Calibration</a>
  - <a href="https://github.com/ros-industrial/industrial_calibration_ros2">Industrial Calibration ROS2 </a>
- Surface Reconstruction
  - <a href="https://github.com/ros-industrial/industrial_reconstruction">Industrial Reconstruction</a>
- Tool Path Planning
  - <a href="https://github.com/ros-industrial/noether">Noether</a>
- Motion Planning
  - <a href="https://github.com/tesseract-robotics">Tesseract</a>
  - <a href="https://github.com/tesseract-robotics/trajopt">Trajopt</a>
  - <a href="https://github.com/ompl/ompl">OMPL</a>
  - <a href="https://github.com/swri-robotics/descartes">Descartes</a>
- Application
  - <a href="https://github.com/BehaviorTree/BehaviorTree.CPP">BehaviorTree.CPP</a>
  - <a href="https://github.com/BehaviorTree/BehaviorTree.ROS2">BehaviorTree.ROS2</a>

